column1: Are you aware that consuming instant or fast-cooking meals may have potential health risks despite being marketed as "natural" or "healthy"?
column2: If you are aware of the potential health risks of instant cooking items, do you still choose them due to convenience?
column3: Do you think FMCG brands intentionally use vague or misleading labels to make their products seem more environmentally friendly?
column4: Would you prefer if FMCG brands provided more detailed information about their ingredients and the environmental impact of their products?
